comments.body:
Can we keep the following in `Reflection`:

```Scala
class TreeMap extends scala.tasty.reflect.TreeMap {
      val reflect: this.type = this
}
```

This way, programmers can just write:

```Scala
new TreeAccumulator[X] { ... }
class MyTreeAccumulator extends TreeAccumulator[X] { ... }
```

Instead of 

```Scala
class MyTreeAccumulator[R <: scala.tasty.Reflection & Singleton](val reflect: R)
extends scala.tasty.reflect.TreeAccumulator[X] { ... }

new scala.tasty.reflect.TreeMap {
    val reflect: qctx.tasty.type = qctx.tasty
    ...
 } 
```
